 the commutation relations: 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\widehat{a}_{\mathbf{k}},\widehat{a}_{\mathbf{k^{\prime}}}^{\dagger}\right]=\delta\left(\mathbf{k}-\mathbf{k^{\prime}}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 The electric and magnetic fields can be obtained according to 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
 &  & \widehat{\mathbf{B}}\left(\mathbf{r}\right)=\mathbf{\boldsymbol{\nabla}}\times\widehat{\mathbf{A}}\left(\mathbf{r}\right)=i\sum_{\mathbf{k}}{\cal E}_{\mathbf{k}}\frac{\mathbf{k}\times\mathbf{e}_{\mathbf{k}}}{c}\left(\widehat{a}_{\mathbf{k}}e^{i\mathbf{k}\cdot\mathbf{r}}-\widehat{a}_{\mathbf{k}}^{\dagger}e^{-i\mathbf{k}\cdot\mathbf{r}}\right),\label{eq:B_operator}\\
 &  & \widehat{\mathbf{E}}_{\perp}\left(\mathbf{r}\right)=-\frac{1}{c}\frac{\partial}{\partial t}\widehat{\mathbf{A}}\left(\mathbf{r}\right)=i\sum_{\mathbf{k}}{\cal E}_{\mathbf{k}}\mathbf{e}_{\mathbf{k}}\left(\widehat{a}_{\mathbf{k}}e^{i\mathbf{k}\cdot\mathbf{r}}-\widehat{a}_{\mathbf{k}}^{\dagger}e^{-i\mathbf{k}\cdot\mathbf{r}}\right),\label{eq:E_operator}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

recalling that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\boldsymbol{\nabla}}\cdot\widehat{\mathbf{A}}\left(\mathbf{r}\right)=0$
\end_inset

 in the Coulomb gauge.
 In term of 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat{\mathbf{E}}$
\end_inset

